Opening (30–60 sec)
• Welcome
• State today's investigation
• Explain why the question matters

The Question (1–2 min)
• Present the central question.
• Explain why sincere believers answer it differently.

Why This Matters (2–4 min)
• Tell a story.
• Share why this investigation exists.
• Invite curiosity instead of defensiveness.

The Evidence (10–20 min)
• Walk through the investigation one section at a time.
• Stay close to the evidence.
• Distinguish:
    - what Scripture says,
    - what history says,
    - what people conclude.

Competing Views (5–10 min)
• Present each major view fairly.
• Explain what each view is trying to protect.

Current Assessment (3–5 min)
• "Here's where I currently land..."
• Explain why.
• Acknowledge remaining uncertainty.

Questions Still Open (2–5 min)
• Read the open questions.
• Invite listeners to investigate with you.

Closing (1–2 min)
• Encourage people to read the passages themselves.
• Point them back to the HomeGroups investigation.
